# The registry index is signed byte-for-byte by the root key, and a
# consumer verifies the detached signature against the exact bytes it
# checks out. Line-ending conversion would change those bytes and
# break verification on any platform whose autocrlf differs from the
# signer's, so pin the signed index and its signature to LF and treat
# the signature as binary (never converted, never diffed).
index.json text eol=lf
index.json.asc -text
